Ok, I&#39;ll just have to stop being such an old fart, ignore the crap that bothers me and move along. If my guys are honest, there isn&#39;t enough time left for anything petty. 

F-S

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;draiga1&quot; &lt;mail@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I am so sorry to hear this, Frank. And I can&#39;t imagine what would possess anyone to try to send any of this type of research to anyone&#39;s job! That is just plain wrong! This research isn&#39;t entirely accepted among the paranormal folks yet, let alone people who aren&#39;t open to aliens, ghosts, or any other unusual things.
&gt; 
&gt; Your box is what started this aspect of research for me. I saw it used on a tv show, and wanted one of my own! I still don&#39;t have a Frank&#39;s box, but feel honored to be on this list with you, and hear the files you&#39;re getting. I don&#39;t understand the nuts and bolts of building a Frank&#39;s box, Steve&#39;s box or Rich&#39;s box, but I am so glad that you guys are out their pushing the envelope in making better and better communication between us and the unseen. 
&gt; 
&gt; There are always going to be people who are set in their own ideas, and not accept anything new. Didn&#39;t they used to think the earth was flat? But then there are always going to be pioneers who know there&#39;s more than meets the eye, and keep working at it no matter who says otherwise. It&#39;s the pioneers of any field that allow new discoveries and allow us all to grow from their efforts. Anyway, that&#39;s my 2 cents, and I hope you stay on the list, even if you take a break for awhile.
&gt; 
&gt; ~Draiga
